cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.HC, cs.LG, cs.SY

This paper is primarily focused on human-robot interaction (HRI) and how robots can collaborate safely and efficiently with humans who exhibit suboptimal behavior. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also discusses modeling human behavior using behavioral economics, which falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper discusses user studies and human cognition, which could fall under the categories of cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper discusses safety and efficiency in HRI, which could fall under the category of cs.SY (Systems and Control).
